      {
        "title": "Great looking, fast as ligtning, lots of fun!",
        "text": "I bought these before the great RAM boom of the 2025 that is currently happening. I seen them go up about 15 dollars in price from when I was originally going to build my gaming PC. I pulled the trigger so to say and bought them before they sky rocketed through the roof thanks to A.I. Companies and theit A.I. Boom needing RAM. Igot lucky. Sorry all you guys out there that need thse. They are fast, accurate, great looking and give me everything I need for my build. I really hope the prices go back down soon so us gamers aren't getting hurt so hard.",
        "user_name": "Bryan",
        "source": "walmart.com",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "7 months ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK2mo19niayRpfFvLZkIoQwY-ePvK_1TNUtto47UgLwAk8YXGiPb81pycV4ZwHHp2tdIZA=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc"
      },
      {
        "text": "This DDR5 has reasonably low latency and timings. In addition to XMP, it supports EXPO which makes it practical for use on AMD platforms. (The older similarly rated Corsair product only had XMP, for Intel platforms.)\n\n6000MHz is a speed that should usually work on Intel or AMD platforms supporting DDR5, while being well above JEDEC default speeds.\n\nThese are specified as 56mm high. The non-RGB Corsair Vengeance are lower. Other makes and models can be as low as between 31 and 32mm. If you will use an air CPU cooler, make sure these will fit.",
        "user_name": "Matt",
        "source": "inet.se/",
